###  http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBI_0100026
<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBI_0100026> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                             owl:equivalentClass [ rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                                                   owl:unionOf ( <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10239>
                                                                                 <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_2>
                                                                                 <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_2157>
                                                                                 <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_2759>
                                                                               )
                                                                 ] ;
                                             rdfs:subClassOf <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000040> ,
                                                             [ owl:intersectionOf ( <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000040>
                                                                                    [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                      owl:onProperty <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0000086> ;
                                                                                      owl:someValuesFrom [ rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                                                                                           owl:unionOf ( <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0001421>
                                                                                                                         <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0001422>
                                                                                                                       )
                                                                                                         ]
                                                                                    ]
                                                                                  ) ;
                                                               rdf:type owl:Class
                                                             ] ;
                                             <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000111> "organism"@en ;
                                             <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000112> "animal"@en ,
                                                                                          "fungus"@en ,
                                                                                          "plant"@en ,
                                                                                          "virus"@en ;
                                             <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000114> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000122> ;
                                             <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115> "A material entity that is an individual living system, such as animal, plant, bacteria or virus, that is capable of replicating or reproducing, growth and maintenance in the right environment. An organism may be unicellular or made up, like humans, of many billions of cells divided into specialized tissues and organs."@en ;
                                             <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000116> "10/21/09: This is a placeholder term, that should ideally be imported from the NCBI taxonomy, but the high level hierarchy there does not suit our needs (includes plasmids and 'other organisms')" ,
                                                                                          """13-02-2009:
OBI doesn't take position as to  when an organism starts or ends being an organism - e.g. sperm, foetus.
This issue is outside the scope of OBI.""" ;
                                             <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000117> "GROUP: OBI Biomaterial Branch" ;
                                             <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000119> "WEB: http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Organism"@en ;
                                             <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000412> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/obi.owl> ;
                                             rdfs:comment """SuMSO developer comment:
Organisms are complex systems. Thus, this ontology branch should be positioned under the “complex system” class.  We did not proceed as such because, for the current purposes of SuMSO, this representation is enough adequate. Implementations will address this aspect in accordance with SCO implementation with regard to system granularity."""@en ,
                                                          """SuMSO developer comment:
We provided the following axiom to ensure reference to life-death:

'material entity' and ('has quality' some (alive or dead))

According to OBI, SuMSO currently classifies viruses as organisms. We leave open the debate of whether viruses are alive or not. 

We strongly envision discussion with subject matter experts to revise this branch, especially with regard to the relationship among organisms, carcasses, and death/life. Even if we included reference to “dead” quality, SuMSO currently does not include carcasses as animals. 

See http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/FOODON_03411564  for consideration of an alternative classification to complement this one. Implementations will equally cover the inclusion of the “multicellular organism” class with this hierarchy, and the reorganization of other subclasses of this ontology branch."""@en ;
                                             rdfs:label "organism"@en .


