###  https://w3id.org/sumso#SuMSO_0000043
<https://w3id.org/sumso#SuMSO_0000043> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                       rdfs:subClassOf <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBI_0000011> ;
                                       rdfs:comment """Currently, SuMSO hierarchically position “activity” classes as subclasses of the “planned process” one. It also describes an activity having interactions as occurrent parts (at least one). Activities can equally have other activities as occurrent parts (sub-activities). 

The position of the class in the hierarchy and the definition require revision. We envision having discussions with subject matter experts about whether an activity is not necessarily planned. We also plan to discuss if an activity requires to have at least two interactions as occurrent parts, to exist or if one is enough.  Similarly, we aim to converse regarding the possibility of introducing the term “action”. Our genuine understanding is that activities have actions as occurrent  parts that have interactions as occurrent  parts."""@en ,
                                                    "Currently, SuMSO reuse classes addressing plan, plan specification, and planned process from the Ontology for Biomedical Investigations ((OBI) and the Information Artifact Ontology (IAO). The Industrial Ontology Foundry (IOF) and Common Core Ontologies (CCO) provide slightly different representations. We plan a deep revision of SuMSO-OBI-IAO representation, envisioning also alignment with those pertaining to IOF and CCO."@en ,
                                                    "Currently, we include the possibility that an activity has as occurrent part (up to solely consist of) only one interaction. We leave open the discussion considering whether an activity requires to have as occurrent parts at least two interactions to exist instead of one."@en ,
                                                    "Further implementations will cover representing plans and plan specifications related to this class, subclasses, and related ones."@en ,
                                                    """SCO interprets agency in relation to interactions. As an activity is composed of interactions, our intuitive understanding is that the agency in an activity should be seen somehow as an integration of the agency(ies) pertaining to the interactions that are part of that activity.

Proposal:
complex system components that are agents in interactions are agents in the activity. Complex system components that are agents in the majority (if not all) interactions that are part of an activity may be considered by some means as the primary agent of the activity.

We leave the discussion open, envisioning conversations with subject matter experts to clarify agency within activities."""@en ,
                                                    "SuMSO must implement to cover classes representing the corresponding spatio-temporal regions and temporal intervals."@en ,
                                                    "This definition requires revision. We envision having discussions with subject matter experts to improve it."@en ;
                                       rdfs:label "complex system activity"@en ;
                                       rdfs:seeAlso """See for possible implementations and alignments:

https://www.ebi.ac.uk/ols4/ontologies/prov/classes/http%253A%252F%252Fwww.w3.org%252Fns%252Fprov%2523Activity 

http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCIT_C43431

http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCIT_C25404

https://bioportal.bioontology.org/ontologies/STY?p=classes&conceptid=T052 

https://bioportal.bioontology.org/ontologies/AURA?p=classes&conceptid=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.projecthalo.com%2Faura%23Activity

https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/core/Core/PlannedProcess 
and subclasses in supply chain ontology and maintenance ontology (IOF ontologies), especially
https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/supplychain/SupplyChain/SupplyChainProcess"""@en ;
                                       <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "A planned process that has as occurrent parts some (at least one) interactions among complex system components or interactions between complex system components and complex system environment components that are causally concatenated to (seeks to) obtain a certain (often planned/desired) output/fulfill a certain (often planned/desired) function."@en ;
                                       <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/core/meta/AnnotationVocabulary/maturity> <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/core/meta/AnnotationVocabulary/Provisional> .


###  https://w3id.org/sumso#SuMSO_0000044
<https://w3id.org/sumso#SuMSO_0000044> rdf:type owl:Class ;
