###  https://w3id.org/sumso#SuMSO_0000048
<https://w3id.org/sumso#SuMSO_0000048> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                       owl:equivalentClass [ owl:intersectionOf ( <https://w3id.org/sumso#SuMSO_0000050>
                                                                                  [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                    owl:onProperty <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000055> ;
                                                                                    owl:someValuesFrom [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                         owl:onProperty <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000059> ;
                                                                                                         owl:someValuesFrom [ owl:intersectionOf ( <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000104>
                                                                                                                                                   [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                                                                     owl:onProperty <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000084> ;
                                                                                                                                                     owl:someValuesFrom <https://w3id.org/sumso#SuMSO_0000024>
                                                                                                                                                   ]
                                                                                                                                                 ) ;
                                                                                                                              rdf:type owl:Class
                                                                                                                            ]
                                                                                                       ]
                                                                                  ]
                                                                                  [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                    owl:onProperty <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000118> ;
                                                                                    owl:someValuesFrom <https://w3id.org/sumso#SuMSO_0000046>
                                                                                  ]
                                                                                  [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                    owl:onProperty <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000118> ;
                                                                                    owl:allValuesFrom <https://w3id.org/sumso#SuMSO_0000046>
                                                                                  ]
                                                                                ) ;
                                                             rdf:type owl:Class
                                                           ] ;
                                       rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/sumso#SuMSO_0000050> ;
                                       rdfs:comment "Possible references to “Farm to Fork” strategies and approaches can be added."@en ;
                                       rdfs:label "food supply chain"@en ;
                                       <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "A supply chain that has as proper occurrent parts some (at least one) food supply chain activities and and realize the plan that concretizes the plan specification that generically depends on at least one food system component."@en ;
                                       <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/core/meta/AnnotationVocabulary/maturity> <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/core/meta/AnnotationVocabulary/Provisional> .


###  https://w3id.org/sumso#SuMSO_0000050
<https://w3id.org/sumso#SuMSO_0000050> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                       rdfs:subClassOf <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBI_0000011> ;
                                       rdfs:comment """Currently, SuMSO represents supply chains as part of complex systems. Supply chain activities are only complex system activities. 

Depending on SCO implementations regarding system granularity, this class and related ones may be revised to represent the transversality and concatenation of supply chains across different systems. A possible tentative approach: we may create classes for complex system environment activities and supply chains may be considered having both system and system environment activities as concatenated occurrent parts."""@en ,
                                                    "Currently, SuMSO reuse classes addressing plan, plan specification, and planned process from the Ontology for Biomedical Investigations ((OBI) and the Information Artifact Ontology (IAO). The Industrial Ontology Foundry (IOF) and Common Core Ontologies (CCO) provide slightly different representations. We plan a deep revision of SuMSO-OBI-IAO representation, envisioning also alignment with those pertaining to IOF and CCO."@en ,
                                                    "Currently, we include the possibility that a supply chain has as occurrent part (up to solely consist of) only one interaction. We leave open the discussion considering whether a supply chain requires to have as occurrent parts at least two activities to exist instead of one."@en ,
                                                    "SuMSO must implement to cover classes representing the corresponding spatio-temporal regions and temporal intervals."@en ;
                                       rdfs:label "supply chain"@en ;
                                       rdfs:seeAlso """See also:
https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/supplychain/SupplyChain/SupplyChainProcess"""@en ;
                                       <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "A planned process that has as proper occurrent parts some (at least one) supply chain activities that are causally concatenated and realize the plan that concretizes the plan specification that generically depends on at lest one complex system component. At least one of the outputs of the activity(-ies) that occurs before is an input for the activity(ies) that follows."@en ;
                                       <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/core/meta/AnnotationVocabulary/maturity> <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/core/meta/AnnotationVocabulary/Provisional> .


###  https://w3id.org/sumso#SuMSO_0000051
<https://w3id.org/sumso#SuMSO_0000051> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                       owl:equivalentClass [ owl:intersectionOf ( <https://w3id.org/sumso#SuMSO_0000043>
                                                                                  [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                    owl:onProperty <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000138> ;
                                                                                    owl:someValuesFrom <https://w3id.org/sumso#SuMSO_0000050>
                                                                                  ]
                                                                                ) ;
                                                             rdf:type owl:Class
                                                           ] ;
                                       rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/sumso#SuMSO_0000043> ;
                                       rdfs:label "supply chain activity"@en ;
                                       <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "A complex system activity that is an occurent part of a supply chain."@en ;
                                       <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/core/meta/AnnotationVocabulary/maturity> <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/core/meta/AnnotationVocabulary/Provisional> .


###  https://w3id.org/sumso#SuMSO_0000053
<https://w3id.org/sumso#SuMSO_0000053> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                       rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/sumso#SuMSO_0000200> ;
                                       owl:disjointWith <https://w3id.org/sumso#SuMSO_0000159> ,
                                                        <https://w3id.org/sumso#SuMSO_0000160> ;
                                       rdfs:label "product-role"@en ;
                                       rdfs:seeAlso """http://purl.allotrope.org/ontologies/role#AFRL_0000018 
http://addictovocab.org/ADDICTO_0001113 
http://addictovocab.org/ADDICTO_0001114""" ;
                                       <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "A role that inheres in a material entity by virtue of realizing in some supply chain activity wherein the bearer is a desired output of that supply chain activity according to the perspective of some corresponding supply chain(s) participants. A product is generally available for sale or purchase along those supply chains."@en ;
                                       <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/core/meta/AnnotationVocabulary/adaptedFrom> """https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/core/Core/MaterialProductRole
http://addictovocab.org/ADDICTO_0001112 
http://purl.allotrope.org/ontologies/role#AFRL_0000360 
http://purl.allotrope.org/ontologies/role#AFRL_0000543""" ;
                                       <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/core/meta/AnnotationVocabulary/maturity> <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/core/meta/AnnotationVocabulary/Released> .


