###  https://w3id.org/sumso#SuMSO_0000159
<https://w3id.org/sumso#SuMSO_0000159> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                       rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/sumso#SuMSO_0000200> ;
                                       owl:disjointWith <https://w3id.org/sumso#SuMSO_0000160> ;
                                       rdfs:label "by-product-role"@en ;
                                       <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "A role that inheres in a material entity by virtue of realizing in some supply chain activity wherein the bearer is an output of that supply chain activity and is perceived as lacking primary relevance according to the perspective of some corresponding supply chain(s) participants. A product may be available for sale or purchase along the corresponding supply chain(s)."@en ;
                                       <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/core/meta/AnnotationVocabulary/adaptedFrom> "http://purl.allotrope.org/ontologies/role#AFRL_0000359" ;
                                       <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/core/meta/AnnotationVocabulary/maturity> <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/core/meta/AnnotationVocabulary/Released> .


###  https://w3id.org/sumso#SuMSO_0000160
<https://w3id.org/sumso#SuMSO_0000160> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                       rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/sumso#SuMSO_0000200> ;
                                       rdfs:label "waste-role"@en ;
                                       <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "A role that inheres in a material entity by virtue of realizing in some supply chain activity wherein the bearer is an output of that supply chain activity and is discarded or not utilized further along the corresponding supply chain(s) because deemed undesirable or perceived as lacking utility or dangerous, according to the perspective of some participants of those supply chains."@en ;
                                       <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/core/meta/AnnotationVocabulary/adaptedFrom> "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01000665" ;
                                       <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/core/meta/AnnotationVocabulary/maturity> <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/core/meta/AnnotationVocabulary/Released> .


###  https://w3id.org/sumso#SuMSO_0000168
<https://w3id.org/sumso#SuMSO_0000168> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                       rdfs:subClassOf <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000015> ;
                                       rdfs:comment "We created this class as a grouping class. Do not use it directly."@en ,
                                                    """We imported these classes as a tentative for representing variations of quality/realizable entities pertaining to meat systems and their components in relation to certain processes, such as supply chain activity. More generally, this is an initial attempt towards representing changing behaviors of behaviors. 

Relations, such as http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0019000, could also be used. 

To represent variations of quality/realizable with respect to different processes, ad hoc relations may be developed. We envision discussions with subject matter experts to deepen this characterization."""@en ;
                                       rdfs:label "increase/decrese/gain/loss of dependent continunat"@en .


